When the logs are in cbor format, there are multiple objects - they are NOT in an array - just objects back to back to back. Example like:

```
{"price":100,"Desc":"Hundred Dollars","level":"info","time":"2019-09-23T11:25:50-07:00"}
{"price":1000,"Desc":"Thousand Dollars","level":"warn","time":"2019-09-23T11:25:50-07:00"}
{"price":1000,"Desc":"Without TS","level":"warn"}
```
load() and loads() just returns the first log line.

One such logger is github.com/rs/zerolog - the binary log format is a CBOR.
